  "commentary": "With SPX at 6592.68 sitting just below the max positive gamma wall at 6605, dealers are likely selling into strength here as they hedge short gamma positions, creating natural resistance. The massive negative GEX at 6500 (-4.77B) and 6400 (-4.60B) means dealers will aggressively buy any dips toward these levels, providing strong support but also amplifying moves if breached. Watch 6605 as the key resistance level where dealer selling intensifies, and monitor the 6500 strike as the critical support where dealer buying should kick in hard.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile swings between 6500 and 6605 with dealers fighting the moves at both ends.",
